# Game/Replay/AnimateMergeStack.elm — EARLY

Replay animation driver for the MergeStack primitive. Companion
to `AnimateSplit` and `AnimateMoveStack`; one of three
synchronous board-drag animators extracted from the former
`prepareReplayStep` in 2026-04-22's REFACTOR_ELM_REPLAY
B1/Axis X.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Shape identical to `AnimateSplit` and
  `AnimateMoveStack` today — the only variable is which
  payload field names the source stack and which WireAction
  constructor wraps the pending action. The per-operation
  module is a place to put primitive-specific divergence if
  it ever earns its own replay animation shape.

## Interface

```elm
start :
    { source : CardStack, target : CardStack, side : Side }
    -> List State.GesturePoint
    -> PathFrame
    -> Model
    -> Float
    -> Maybe Space.AnimationInfo
```

Returns Nothing only when the source stack can't be resolved
against the current board.

## Dependencies

- `Game.Replay.Space` — for `boardStackSource` and
  `AnimationInfo`.
- `Game.BoardActions` — for the `Side` type in the payload.
- `Game.WireAction` — for `WA.MergeStack`.
- `Main.State` — for `Model`, `PathFrame`, `GesturePoint`.

## Pointers

- Called from `Game.Replay.Time.startBoardAnim`'s
  `WA.MergeStack payload ->` branch.
- Companion modules: `AnimateSplit`, `AnimateMoveStack`.
